values.description:
Provides basic `/models` and `/worlds` routes. We can remove this once the backend is ready.


models:

* GET /models

* GET /models/:id

* POST /models

* DEL /models/:id

worlds:

* GET /worlds

* GET /worlds/:id

* POST /worlds

* DEL /worlds/:id

First run `npm install` first in the `test-server` directory to install the node modules. Run `npm start` to start the node server and you'll be able to access the routes, e.g,:

~~~
http://localhost:8001/1.0/models
~~~

values.description:
This pull request allows reading models on cache on disk. Here is an example of a cache file structure:

```
LocalCache_TEST6
├── alice
│   ├── am1
│   │   └── model.config
│   └── am2
│       └── model.config
├── bob
│   ├── bm1
│   │   └── model.config
│   └── bm2
│       └── model.config
└── trudy
    ├── tm1
    │   └── model.config
    └── tm2
        └── model.config
LocalCache_TEST3
├── alice
│   └── am1
│       └── model.config
├── bob
│   └── bm1
│       └── model.config
└── trudy
    └── tm1
        └── model.config
```
The level directories are servers. They have a local name on disk. There are two servers above. The next level are owners. After that are models. A directory is considered a model as long as it has a file called `model.config`.

The `LocalCache` is integrated with the `FuelClient`. If servers can't be contacted, the `FuelClient` will return models from cache instead. The local cache supports fetching all models, some models (partial match of source, owner, or name), or one specific model by UniqueName()


#TODO

* Model Fetch should check LocalCache first. This will be another pull request.

```

http://localhost:8001/alice/am1
http://localhost:8001/alice/am2
http://localhost:8001/alice/am3
```

```
$ ign fuel list --name am1
http://localhost:8001/alice/am1
```

```
$ ign fuel list --owner bob 
http://localhost:8001/bob/bm2
http://localhost:8001/bob/bm1
http://localhost:8001/bob/bm3
```

```
$ ign fuel pull --owner asdf --name asdf
TODO Download a model
```

```
$ ign fuel push --owner asdf --name asdf --url todo --path /tmp/asdf
TODO Upload a model
```

```

/build/ign-fuel-tools/local/alice/am3
